Are you also having difficulties? I did the same as you

Guys, guys guys. It's not that hard. This mod installs the same as any other.

  • Drag and drop the "Launchers Pack" folder into your GameData directory, that's it. It is literally all you need to do.
  • If you want switchable textures, install firespitter (again, drag and drop "Firespitter" folder into GameData).
  • If you want reflections on some of the parts, like the engines, install Texture Replacer (again, drag and drop the "Texture Replacer" folder into GameData).
Edited May 4, 2017 by liquidhype

@Commander223323

You have a big Chaos in your GameData. No wonder that it didn't work.

Never get a GameData into GameData. The BD-Extras are wrong beacause you must copy them in your Bluedog-Folder and overwrite the existing files. The Ships-Folder must be in the Save-Game, not GameData.

The Laztek-Launcherspack is for 0.90 and did not work in 1.2.2 and the SpaceX-folder of this must be in a Launchers Pack Folder. So the right path is GameData\Launchers Pack\SpaceX not GameData\SpaceX. Look at the folder-structure of this download.
